---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'India Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/india/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
  { title: 'Sri Lanka for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/sri-lanka' },
  { title: 'Nepal for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/nepal' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'indiaFit', header: 'India Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '₹25,000-36,000/mo', indiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '₹29,500-42,000/mo', indiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '₹22,500-32,500/mo', indiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '₹21,000-30,000/mo', indiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Indian Local', entryAge: '65-70', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: '₹5,000-15,000/mo', indiaFit: 'Domestic Only' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '₹22,500-36,000', annual: '₹2.7L-4.3L' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '₹31,000-48,000', annual: '₹3.7L-5.8L' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '₹42,000-64,000', annual: '₹5L-7.7L' },
  { category: 'India Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: '₹500-2,000/visit' },
  { category: 'India Public', monthly: 'Free/nominal', annual: 'Variable quality' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in India 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in India. Medical tourism, spiritual retreats, affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in India"
  subheadline="India offers world-class medical tourism, spiritual retreats, incredible diversity, and extremely affordable living—a unique retirement destination for the adventurous."
  heroImage="/images/countries/india-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose India</h2>
  <p>
    India offers extraordinary value and diversity—world-class hospitals at fraction of Western prices, spiritual retreats, ancient culture, and extremely affordable living. For those with Indian connections or seeking deep cultural immersion, India is unmatched. The challenge is navigating complexity.
  </p>

  <p>
    Goa offers beach lifestyle with established expat community. Kerala provides Ayurveda and backwaters. Rajasthan offers desert heritage. Rishikesh attracts spiritual seekers. Pondicherry has French colonial charm. Major cities have best healthcare. Each region is essentially a different country.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent private; world-class in major cities</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Hindi + regional; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> ₹50,000-150,000/month (~$600-1,800); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Varies enormously by region</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Spiritual; diverse; chaotic; rewarding</li>
      <li><strong>Medical Tourism:</strong> Global leader in affordable procedures</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">India Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    India has excellent private healthcare—Apollo, Fortis, Max, Medanta are world-class. Medical tourism is major industry. Procedures cost 60-80% less than Western countries. Major cities (Delhi, Mumbai, Chennai, Bangalore) have outstanding facilities. Quality varies greatly outside major hospitals.
  </p>

  <p>
    For medical tourism procedures, India is among the world best values. International insurance provides access to top private hospitals. For seniors living in India, proximity to quality healthcare should guide location choice.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Medical Tourism Leader</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      India is a global medical tourism leader—cardiac surgery, orthopedics, oncology at world-class quality for fraction of Western prices. Apollo, Fortis hospitals rival any in the world. International insurance ensures access to these top facilities.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    India has various visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>X Visa (Entry Visa)</h3>
  <p>
    For long-term stay including retirement. Requires sponsorship or demonstrable reason for extended stay. Up to 5-year validity possible. Registration with FRRO required.
  </p>

  <h3>Medical Visa (M Visa)</h3>
  <p>
    For medical treatment at recognized hospitals. Up to 1 year, extendable. Useful for medical tourism stays.
  </p>

  <h3>E-Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-day to 1-year electronic visa. Easy to obtain. Some retirees use extended tourist visa while exploring longer options.
  </p>

  <h3>OCI (Overseas Citizen of India)</h3>
  <p>
    For people of Indian origin—lifetime visa with unrestricted stay. Ideal for NRIs returning for retirement.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for India:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Long-term visa:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Important for private hospital access</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> Provides top hospital access</li>
    <li><strong>Local option:</strong> Indian insurers available for residents</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for India</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with India coverage ensures access to Apollo, Fortis, and other top private hospitals. Private healthcare is very affordable even without insurance, but coverage provides security and access to premium facilities.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in India, comprehensive coverage with top hospital access works well:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for India</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong India network, top hospital access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Asia expertise, good India coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive regional pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers with strong India networks.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for India are moderate given excellent healthcare access:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Indian private care is very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Consultations ₹500-1,500; very cheap</li>
    <li><strong>Procedure pricing:</strong> Even major procedures are affordable cash</li>
    <li><strong>Location choice:</strong> Choose retirement location near quality hospitals</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: NRI Returning, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> OCI card holder, $2,000/month pension. Mumbai return.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> OCI status. Cigna Global with India and US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~₹28,000/month (~$330). Family connections; world-class healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Spiritual Seeker, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £1,500/month pension. Rishikesh yoga lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> X Visa. BUPA Global. Delhi for serious healthcare.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~₹35,000/month (~£350). Spiritual immersion; Himalayas.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German Goa Seeker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,400/month pension. Goa beach lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> E-Visa to X-Visa. Allianz Care with European backup.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Allianz ~₹24,000/month (~€280). Beach life; expat community.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is India overwhelming for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Can be—depends on personality and previous exposure. Those with Indian connections or prior travel adapt easily. First-timers may find it challenging. Start with more organized areas (Goa, Kerala, Pondicherry). Build experience gradually. Rewarding for adaptable personalities.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is India really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extremely affordable—among world lowest costs. Comfortable retirement possible on $800-1,500/month. Local food, domestic help, and services very cheap. Imported goods and Western lifestyle cost more. Can live very well on modest pension.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Indian healthcare safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Top private hospitals are world-class—JCI accredited, Western-trained doctors, modern equipment. Medical tourism reputation is earned. Quality varies greatly; stick to recognized hospital groups. Not all facilities are equal; choose carefully.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about long-term visa complexity?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        India visa system is bureaucratic—FRRO registration, renewals, paperwork. OCI holders have it easier. Non-Indian expats need patience. Consider hiring visa consultant. Bureaucracy is real challenge but manageable with support.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with strong India coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Indian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
